message.content:
■ Analysis of Main Target Image

1) Overall Count and Layering

The model naturally divides into two “groups” of blocks (a left group and a right group).  In total there are 16 blocks used, arranged in multiple layers:

• Left Group (9 blocks total)
  – Bottom Layer: 3 red arches side‐by‐side.  
  – Second Layer (resting on the arches): one blue cube, one yellow half‐cylinder, and one orange cube.  
  – Behind/Above those cubes (forming the “third layer”): one tall green rectangular block flanked by two tall yellow rectangular blocks.

• Right Group (7 blocks total)
  – Bottom Layer: 2 red arches side‐by‐side.  
  – Second Layer: a wide yellow rectangular block spanning across the two arches.  
  – Third Layer: another red arch set on top of that wide yellow block.  
  – Fourth Layer: a narrower yellow rectangular block inserted through (or bridging) the red arch.  
  – Top Layer: two orange triangular wedges (mirrored) forming a “roof.”

2) Selecting the Required Blocks from the Dictionary

Matching each shape, color, and orientation exactly (without rotating any dictionary blocks), the following indices are used:

• Red Arches (index 1) – 6 total  
• Blue Cube (index 6) – 1 total  
• Orange Cube (index 7) – 1 total  
• Green Tall Rectangular Block (index 8) – 1 total  
• Narrow Yellow Rectangular Block (index 9) – 1 total  
• Tall Yellow Rectangular Block (index 11) – 2 total  
• Wide Yellow Rectangular Block (index 13) – 1 total  
• Yellow Half‐Cylinder (index 14) – 1 total  
• Orange Triangular Wedge, left‐leaning (index 15) – 1 total  
• Orange Triangular Wedge, right‐leaning (index 16) – 1 total  

3) Step‐by‐Step Assembly Order

Below is one possible build sequence.  Use the indicated block indices in exactly that order:

{
  "Step1": "Move block with index 1 (red arch) for left-group base, left side",
  "Step2": "Move block with index 1 (red arch) for left-group base, center",
  "Step3": "Move block with index 1 (red arch) for left-group base, right side",
  "Step4": "Move block with index 6 (blue cube) on top of left arch",
  "Step5": "Move block with index 14 (yellow half-cylinder) on top of center arch",
  "Step6": "Move block with index 7 (orange cube) on top of right arch",
  "Step7": "Move block with index 8 (green tall block) behind the half-cylinder",
  "Step8": "Move block with index 11 (tall yellow block) behind/next to green block",
  "Step9": "Move block with index 11 (tall yellow block) behind/next to green block (other side)",
  "Step10": "Move block with index 1 (red arch) for right-group base, left side",
  "Step11": "Move block with index 1 (red arch) for right-group base, right side",
  "Step12": "Move block with index 13 (wide yellow rectangle) bridging those two arches",
  "Step13": "Move block with index 1 (red arch) on top of the wide yellow rectangle",
  "Step14": "Move block with index 9 (narrow yellow rectangle) through the top arch",
  "Step15": "Move block with index 15 (orange wedge) as left half of roof",
  "Step16": "Move block with index 16 (orange wedge) as right half of roof"
}
